article.headline: Records scores 17 as Colgate downs Navy 88-64
article.description: — Keegan Records had 17 points in Colgate's 88-64 win over Navy on Saturday; its seventh-straight win.
article.linkText: Records scores 17 as Colgate downs Navy 88-64
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- — Keegan Records had 17 points in Colgate's 88-64 win over Navy on Saturday; its seventh-straight win. Records added eight rebounds for the Raiders (15-8, 9-1 Patriot League). Braeden Smith scored 14 points and added five assists. Brady Cummins had 12 points and was 4 of 8 shooting (4 for 7 from 3-point range). The Raiders never trailed. Mike Woods led the Midshipmen (8-13, 4-6) in scoring, finishing with 16 points, six rebounds and two steals. Austin Benigni added 15 points and five assists for Navy. In addition, Austin Inge finished with 10 points and three steals. Both teams next play Wednesday. Colgate visits Boston University and Navy plays Bucknell at home. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
